     1	# Resumable Git Audit Pipeline
     2	
     3	This runbook turns Git audit and reviewer handoff into a recoverable workflow rather than a chat-only memory exercise.
     4	
     5	## Goal
     6	
     7	Use this workflow whenever implementation, audit, and Git closeout may span multiple executors or multiple interrupted sessions.
     8	
     9	The point is not to find one perfect reviewer. The point is to preserve enough state that a different reviewer or CLI session can resume safely.
    10	
    11	## Core Roles
    12	
    13	| Role | Responsibility |
    14	|---|---|
    15	| `Planner` | Freeze truth sources, allowed files, validation, and acceptance boundary |
    16	| `Executor` | Perform the bounded implementation or investigation |
    17	| `Auditor` | Review the result, risks, and validation status |
    18	| `Gatekeeper` | Run hard gates outside the semantic auditor when possible |
    19	| `Owner Review` | Final acceptance, conflict resolution, and Git closeout |
    20	
