1. Root state truth is currently false. Category: `current bug`. Evidence: [`session_state.md`](/Users/mac/Desktop/agent-framework-template/session_state.md#L8) still says the active goal is to close out the SKILL follow-up and that there is “No active work” with “Independent review, then git closeout” next, even though the file also records that wave as completed and the roadmap is already through Phase 3 in [`ROADMAP.md`](/Users/mac/Desktop/agent-framework-template/ROADMAP.md#L41). Why it matters to adopters: this repo is supposed to prove session-state discipline by example, and it currently demonstrates the opposite. Smallest honest fix now: update or rotate the root [`session_state.md`](/Users/mac/Desktop/agent-framework-template/session_state.md#L1) immediately, then add one self-hosting validator check so the template repo fails when its root state is obviously stale instead of only validating [`templates/session_state.template.md`](/Users/mac/Desktop/agent-framework-template/scripts/validate_template.py#L635).

2. The execution-contract surface is presented as operationally required, but it is still mostly a documentation ritual. Category: `doc overclaim`. Evidence: README says “Before any long-running or multi-step task, the agent should produce an execution contract” in [`README.md`](/Users/mac/Desktop/agent-framework-template/README.md#L200), the adoption guide repeats that in [`docs/ADOPTION_GUIDE.md`](/Users/mac/Desktop/agent-framework-template/docs/ADOPTION_GUIDE.md#L233), and the implementer agent says it will not enter autonomous execution until confirmed in [`.github/agents/implementer.agent.md`](/Users/mac/Desktop/agent-framework-template/.github/agents/implementer.agent.md#L68). But the validator only checks that the template contains certain strings in [`scripts/validate_template.py`](/Users/mac/Desktop/agent-framework-template/scripts/validate_template.py#L651), and the repo ships no completed execution-contract example or enforcement path proving adopters will actually use it. Why it matters to adopters: they may believe commit ownership, closeout boundary, and validation gate behavior are operationally settled when they are still dependent on agent obedience. Smallest honest fix now: either ship one filled execution-contract example in the demo path, or soften the README/adoption wording from expected behavior to recommended practice until there is executable proof.

3. Proof-vs-claim discipline is only partially real; the closeout audit is a heuristic and optional for adopters. Category: `governance gap`. Evidence: the audit only regex-matches claims and any anchor-like line in the same diff in [`scripts/closeout_truth_audit.py`](/Users/mac/Desktop/agent-framework-template/scripts/closeout_truth_audit.py#L13), and hook enforcement exists only when adopters install the optional hooks in [`.githooks/pre-commit`](/Users/mac/Desktop/agent-framework-template/.githooks/pre-commit#L1). The repo does test that hook path in [`tests/test_hook_scaffolding.py`](/Users/mac/Desktop/agent-framework-template/tests/test_hook_scaffolding.py#L82), but the rule in [`.github/copilot-instructions.md`](/Users/mac/Desktop/agent-framework-template/.github/copilot-instructions.md#L1016) reads stronger than what is mechanically guaranteed. Why it matters to adopters: they can think they inherited strong closeout-proof governance when they actually inherited a lightweight anti-placeholder check plus optional installation. Smallest honest fix now: document this as a heuristic guard unless hooks are installed, and tighten the accepted anchors to explicit receipt-shaped evidence instead of any matching line like `N passed`.

**One Thing The Packet Is Over-Worried About**

The packet is over-worried that git closeout policy is still too abstract. That part is more mature than it gives credit for: the repo has a concrete runbook in [`docs/runbooks/resumable-git-audit-pipeline.md`](/Users/mac/Desktop/agent-framework-template/docs/runbooks/resumable-git-audit-pipeline.md#L5), a pre-commit closeout audit hook in [`.githooks/pre-commit`](/Users/mac/Desktop/agent-framework-template/.githooks/pre-commit#L1), and tests proving the hook blocks unanchored closeout claims in [`tests/test_hook_scaffolding.py`](/Users/mac/Desktop/agent-framework-template/tests/test_hook_scaffolding.py#L82). The weakness is not absence of a model; it is optionality and self-hosting inconsistency.

**Final Recommendation**

`patch now`

The fixes are small and honesty-restoring: repair root state, add one self-hosting stale-state check, and either prove the execution-contract path with one concrete example or soften the current wording.
